about:
I am a software engineer and a fourth-year Information Systems student at Addis Ababa University. In addition to my university studies, I am also an aspiring MERN stack developer, currently enrolled in advanced courses at Yenetta Code.


 I have the honor of serving as the Tech Club President at Addis Ababa University, where I lead various initiatives and projects.
My passion for coding is evident in my dedication and hard work. Over the years, I have undertaken and successfully completed numerous projects, continually expanding my skills and knowledge in the field of software development. My commitment to excellence and continuous learning drives me to stay updated with the latest technologies and development practices.
